    "body": "You can't rely on the same trick used by `tcmalloc` and `jemalloc` because it implies dynamic linking. It only works if the application dynamically links against the standard C library and it uses weak symbols. The real solution for the allocator is to use the `je_` prefix and extend LLVM's detection of `malloc` and `free` to them.\n",
