    "created_at": "2013-11-15T13:24:06Z",
    "updated_at": "2013-11-15T13:24:48Z",
    "body": "I don't think it makes sense to override these. Thanks to inter-procedural optimization, you cannot replace functions defined in a compiled binary with alternate functions. It's possible to override weak symbols defined in a dynamic library like `malloc` and `free`, and I think that's enough. Since we aren't using `jemalloc` anymore there's nothing preventing the usual weak symbol override.\n",
